<h1 class="hero-h">ChatGPT vs Gemini: <em>honest 2026 comparison.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">ChatGPT and Gemini are the two highest-volume general-purpose AI assistants. They look similar from the outside but trade off differently on ecosystem, reasoning, multimodality, and price.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short answer</div><p class="verdict-p">ChatGPT is the default if you want the largest plugin/ecosystem and the most mature business plan. Gemini is the default if you live inside Google Workspace and want native integration with Docs, Sheets, Gmail, and Drive. For B2B teams already on Workspace, Gemini wins on workflow friction. For everyone else, ChatGPT is usually the safer first pick.</p></div>
<p class="note">Pricing references are as of June 2026 and may change. Always verify on each vendor's site before committing.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">ChatGPT: where it wins</h2>
<p class="body">OpenAI's ChatGPT is the most-used AI assistant and the most mature business product on the market. It has the broadest third-party ecosystem and the most familiar product surface.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Largest ecosystem.</strong> Most third-party tools, GPTs, and integrations target ChatGPT first.</li>
<li><strong>Mature business plan.</strong> ChatGPT Team and Enterprise have well-developed admin, data, and SSO controls.</li>
<li><strong>Strong default reasoning.</strong> The frontier reasoning models are competitive at the top of every benchmark that matters for business work.</li>
<li><strong>Familiarity.</strong> Almost everyone has used it, which lowers your team's adoption curve.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Gemini: where it wins</h2>
<p class="body">Google's Gemini is deeply integrated into Workspace. If your team already lives in Docs, Sheets, Gmail, and Drive, Gemini is right there inside those tools.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Native Workspace integration.</strong> Acts on emails, documents, and sheets in place without copy-paste.</li>
<li><strong>Strong multimodality.</strong> Image and video understanding is competitive and tightly integrated with Google products.</li>
<li><strong>Free tier and inclusion in Workspace.</strong> Often comes bundled with plans your team already pays for.</li>
<li><strong>Large context for retrieval-style work.</strong> Useful for summarizing or querying long internal documents.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Side-by-side</h2>
<p class="body">A direct, dimension-by-dimension look. Use this as a quick scan, then read the decision framework below.</p>
<table class="cmp-table">
<thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>ChatGPT</th><th>Gemini</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Sweet spot</td><td>General purpose, broad ecosystem</td><td>Inside Google Workspace</td></tr>
<tr><td>Best for</td><td>Most B2B teams without strong Google preference</td><td>Teams already deep in Docs/Sheets/Gmail</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pricing model</td><td>Per-seat Plus/Team/Enterprise; API by token</td><td>Per-seat or bundled with Workspace plans</td></tr>
<tr><td>Multimodality</td><td>Image, voice, code; agents</td><td>Image, video, integrated with Google Photos/Drive</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ecosystem</td><td>Largest 3rd-party integrations</td><td>Native with Google products</td></tr>
<tr><td>Adoption curve</td><td>Lowest (everyone has used it)</td><td>Low if already on Workspace</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When to choose ChatGPT</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You are not on Google Workspace, or your team uses many non-Google tools.</li>
<li>You want the broadest third-party integration ecosystem.</li>
<li>You need admin features (SSO, data controls, audit logs) and want the most mature business plan.</li>
<li>You want the lowest team-adoption curve.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When to choose Gemini</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Your team lives in Docs, Sheets, Gmail, and Drive.</li>
<li>You want AI that acts on documents and email in place, not in a separate window.</li>
<li>You need strong video and image understanding tied to Google's media tools.</li>
<li>You already pay for a Workspace plan that bundles Gemini, and want to consolidate.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When most teams should run both</h2>
<p class="body">Running both for different workflows is common in larger B2B teams. Gemini handles work that lives inside Workspace; ChatGPT handles cross-tool work and one-off projects.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Marketing and operations teams keep Gemini for the inside-Workspace flow; product and engineering use ChatGPT for cross-tool work.</li>
<li>Larger organizations standardize on one for the company and let individuals add the other on their own plan.</li>
<li>Compliance-heavy teams pick the one whose data terms match their requirements and stick to it.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Combined seat cost is small relative to the productivity lift from picking the right tool for each job. The wrong move is buying one because it is cheaper and forcing it into work it is not built for.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is ChatGPT or Gemini better for business?</div><div class="faq-a">ChatGPT has the more mature business plan as of June 2026 and a larger third-party ecosystem. Gemini is better when your team already works inside Google Workspace, because it acts on those tools natively. The right answer depends more on your stack than on raw model quality.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is Gemini free with Google Workspace?</div><div class="faq-a">Google has bundled Gemini access into several Workspace tiers. The exact inclusion changes; verify on the current Workspace pricing page. Even free, Gemini is a strong default for teams already paying for Workspace.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can I use both?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes, and many companies do. Combined seat costs are modest, and the right tool for each workflow saves more than running both.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Which is better at reasoning?</div><div class="faq-a">Both are at the frontier as of June 2026. The differences on standard reasoning benchmarks are smaller than the differences in integration and ecosystem, which is usually what determines adoption.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Which is safer for proprietary data?</div><div class="faq-a">Both vendors offer business and enterprise tiers with stronger data terms (no training on your inputs, SSO, audit logs). Read each plan's data-handling page and pick the tier that matches your compliance needs.</div></div>
</div></section>

